<DOC><DOCNO> AP891222-0086 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-22-89 1037EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-SalvationArmyClosed 1stLd-Writethru a0502 12-22 0242</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Salvation Army Closed, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0502,0241</SECOND><HEAD>New Bedford Salvation Army Saved From Shutting Its Doors</HEAD><HEAD>Eds: UPDATES throughout with office reopened because of surge indonations. No pickup. Removes BRF designation.</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW BEDFORD, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Word that the Salvation Army in thiseconomically troubled city would be closed for the rest of theholiday season for lack of funds brought a flood of donations,allowing the office to reopen, an official said today.   ``The outpouring of the public has been marvelous,'' Maj. RobertPfeiffer, who runs the office, said this morning. Pfeiffer saidseveral thousand dollars was donated by corporations andindividuals after word of the closing went out.   ``We are not turning anyone away,'' Pfeiffer said. ``TheSalvation Army is alive and well in New Bedford.''   Pfeiffer announced Thursday that the office would closeindefinitely, saying a sharp increase in the number of peopleseeking assistance was to blame.When the doors were closed at 2p.m., there were still about 100 people waiting for help, he said.   ``We've gone into using the canned food we had put aside forJanuary and February,'' Pfeiffer said Thursday.   Pfeiffer blamed unemployment for bringing 1,600 families to theoffice in the past year _ 300 more than last year. There have beenabout 1,000 layoffs in the area in the last month, he said.   The Salvation Army is a national religious and charitableorganization that is organized along military lines.</TEXT></DOC>